content.description: Fun climb with good pockets past a few overhanging bulges.
content.location: To the right of Julie's Kiss. This climbs the center line of bolts on the belay ledge.

content.description: Short and pumpy, big ledges and jugs.
content.protection: 4 bolts, bolted anchor with rap rings.
content.location: Back wall of the Comic Gallery, to the left of the cave. Only bolted line on the back wall.

content.description: Overhung juggy, often dirty due to little traffic.
content.location: Right of He-Man, next route left of Taz.

content.description: short easy section to a short roof and bulge.
content.location: To the right of Super Fly, starts up on belay ledge. Climbs the left most route, shares first one or two bolts with Three Strikes.

content.description: Shares the first two bolts with Flash, then continues to the right of Flash to its own chains. One muddy pocket under the overhang.
content.location: Shares start with Flash, then moves right, Left of Skeletor.

content.description: Climbs the big overhanging bulge the whole way up. Super Classic jug haul.
content.protection: 6 bolts, hangers. Last bolt before face is a spinner.
content.location: Shares first two bolts with He Man, To the right of The Buddha. climbs the overhang on the left side of the Comic Gallery.

climbs.name: Exquze me, do you have any Grey Poupon?

content.description: Tends to have more sloppy pockets then Three Strikes, grade may not be as consistent through the whole route.
content.location: From the belay ledge, this takes the route on the far right, to the right of Three Strikes.

content.description: A little overgrown from low traffic, slightly overhanging.
content.protection: 7 bolts (first three shared with Flash), Fixe anchors.
content.location: To the left of Flash, starts with the first three bolts of Flash, then moves to the left.

content.description:
Small U shaped wall with 5.10 and hard sport climbs, generally steep and juggy. If it has rained this area is pretty much unclimbable. This area houses one of Pictured  Rocks' most popular climbs - Flash! 

  Note: Julie's Kiss, Three Strikes No Balls, and Exquze me, do you have any Grey Poupon? are best accessed by climbing up a small boulder(to the right of Super Fly) to a belay ledge.
